<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Vanced Whiteheart</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-08-23 15:31:37</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>To settle the arguements we High Elves cannot wear this fine ear ring... but suck it up guys and show how proud the race is suppose to be and carry on ... but here are the stats and proof of them .. as well as details as I have found out on the quest, because I to looked into it in seach of the earings for myself a humble cleric ...<BR>
Good luck to all in the quest...<BR>
<BR>
Ivandyr's Hoop:  AC 6.  6 charges of Spirit Tap, +6 Wis, +6 Int, +6 Hp. Races:  Hum, Erud,  DE, Gno, Half Elf, Troll, Ogre.  Classes:  C, E, Mg, N, Ra,Ro, SK, Sm, Wr, Wz. <BR>
<BR>
Here is the proof to settle all doubt.. <BR>
<BR>
http://everquest.allakhazam.com/equipment/graphics/Ivander's_Hoop.htm<BR>
<BR>
In the Innothule swamp, you talk to Lynuga, a wandering NPC troll female that can usually be found near the entrance to Guk. After level 10 or so she will tell you that she collects gems. By the upper teens, she will tell you about her gem collection and that she wants more. Ask her what gems and she will tell you that she wants a ruby. You can buy the ruby at most jewelry stores. In return for the ruby, she gives one of several items. Ones I know of are the Brutechopper axe, Midnight Mallet and Ivandyr's Hoop. FYI, giving her chomper's ruby from Rivervale will not work. The criteria for what you get seems unclear and could just be random. However, someone with a lot of time and money on their hands stated that she gave him a hoop every 20th gem, so it may just be that you have to do it a lot to get the good items. <BR>
<BR>
Vanced Whiteheart<BR>
Cleric & Sage of Tunare<BR>
Wyrmlore Council<BR>
</font></td></tr></table>
