<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Nileya</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-08-25 17:50:42</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Okay here's the deal. Lynuga is a random spawn. She spawns, in fact, quite often. To the above post, this item is not rechargable. I've received 7 hoops from her.<BR>
<BR>
The first time I tried it I got it one the fifth ruby. Thank God too because that was all I had.<BR>
<BR>
The second and third time, I was with one of my guildmates, using another character. We pooled together about 2000pp. We got the first one on the 8th try. The second on the 10th.<BR>
<BR>
My guildmate traded his hoop in for a MoSS. Very nice weapon I might add. So he wanted another, as well as I, having traded mine too. This time, however, it turned into a guild event. Four of us were to try our luck. So once again we pooled all our money into rubies. We're talking about 8000pp. We decided that 2000pp to get one would be sufficient. As shadow knights, we cast a siphon strength on her and pulled her to the hand. Why you might ask? This way we could sell all brutechoppers and midnight mallets whenever she gave us one. I would do the quests. And whenever we got a hoop, I would give it to the one who shelled out the most money first. After 41 rubies, nothing. We tried another stack. On the first ruby...HOOP! Five more another hoop. One of my guildmates ran off to Grobb with the cash I had been receiving from all the axes and hammers we were getting to buy more rubies, just in case we needed them.<BR>
<BR>
HINT: Always sell everytime between giving her a ruby wearing your best CHA gear. You should be able to sell the axes and hammers for a little bit than half the cost of a ruby. And hail her each time you give her one to keep her there or she will run off again.<BR>
<BR>
After our third stack, one of our guildmates got restless and gave her a ruby as well. Boom! Hoop. Fourth stack, we got another. Fifth stack, on the 11th ruby, another. This one was mine. We gave her 4 more rubies before someone pulled and killed her.<BR>
<BR>
So in 95 rubies, we got 4. Not including my restless guildmate. But if you want to then we got 5 in about 100. This averages out to 1 out of 20. The item she gives is completely random. I've heard, though I can't confirm, that the item she gives depends on the time you give it to her. Much like how a random roll works when your group rolls for an item. This is something I believe. It all depends on when you push that GIVE button.<BR>
<BR>
Nileya<BR>
Quellious</font></td></tr></table>
